# Merfolk Extension Configuration Demo

This demo shows how the new preview column configuration works.

## Testing Mermaid File Preview Column

1. Open this .mmd file in VSCode
2. Check the extension settings for "merfolk.preview.defaultColumn"
3. Try different values and see where the preview opens

## Testing Inline Preview Column

1. Open a .md file with mermaid blocks
2. Check the extension settings for "merfolk.inlinePreview.defaultColumn"
3. Try different values and see where the inline preview opens

## Configuration Options

### merfolk.preview.defaultColumn
- `beside`: Opens beside current editor (default)
- `right`: Opens in rightmost column
- `left`: Opens in leftmost column
- `active`: Opens in current column
- `one`: Opens in column one
- `two`: Opens in column two
- `three`: Opens in column three

### merfolk.inlinePreview.defaultColumn
- `right`: Opens in rightmost column (default)
- `beside`: Opens beside current editor
- `left`: Opens in leftmost column
- `active`: Opens in current column
- `one`: Opens in column one
- `two`: Opens in column two
- `three`: Opens in column three

